SEC. 2. The ceramic processing plant shall have the following functions;

Study the efficient utilization of ceramic raw materials of the locality;

Process and compound whatever clay or other ceramic raw materials may be found in the locality for sale to potters at cost;

Mix ceramic materials for glaze to be sold at cost to potters;

Construct a community kiln for use of local potters at nominal cost;

Teach, guide and demonstrate to local potters the making of different kinds of ceramic products such as structural hollow clay blocks, building bricks, tiles, and household potter wares like flower vases, art wares, containers, dinnerwares, drinking vessels, insulators, etc; and

Conduct such researches or studies as may be necessary for the efficient and effective functioning of the plant.
